info.description: Atlas exposes a variety of REST endpoints to work with types, entities, lineage and data discovery.
info.title: Atlas REST API

tags.name: DiscoveryREST
tags.description: REST interface for data discovery using dsl or full text search.

tags.name: LineageREST
tags.description: REST interface for an entity's lineage information.

tags.name: TypesREST
tags.description: REST interface for CRUD operations on type definitions.

json_AtlasAttributeDef.title: AtlasAttributeDef
json_AtlasAttributeDef.description: class that captures details of a struct-attribute.

json_AtlasBaseTypeDef.title: AtlasBaseTypeDef
json_AtlasBaseTypeDef.description: Base class that captures common-attributes for all Atlas types.

json_AtlasClassification.title: AtlasClassification
json_AtlasClassification.description: An instance of a classification; it doesn't have an identity, this object exists only when associated with an entity.

json_AtlasClassificationDef.title: AtlasClassificationDef
json_AtlasClassificationDef.description: class that captures details of a classification-type.

json_AtlasConstraintDef.title: AtlasConstraintDef
json_AtlasConstraintDef.description: class that captures details of a constraint.

json_AtlasEntitiesWithExtInfo.title: AtlasEntitiesWithExtInfo
json_AtlasEntitiesWithExtInfo.description: An instance of an entity along with extended info - like hive_table, hive_database.

json_AtlasEntity.title: AtlasEntity
json_AtlasEntity.description: An instance of an entity - like hive_table, hive_database.

json_AtlasEntityDef.title: AtlasEntityDef
json_AtlasEntityDef.description: class that captures details of a entity-type.

json_AtlasEntityExtInfo.title: AtlasEntityExtInfo
json_AtlasEntityExtInfo.description: An instance of an entity along with extended info - like hive_table, hive_database.

json_AtlasEntityHeader.title: AtlasEntityHeader
json_AtlasEntityHeader.description: An instance of an entity - like hive_table, hive_database.

json_AtlasEntityWithExtInfo.title: AtlasEntityWithExtInfo
json_AtlasEntityWithExtInfo.description: An instance of an entity along with extended info - like hive_table, hive_database.

json_AtlasEnumDef.title: AtlasEnumDef
json_AtlasEnumDef.description: class that captures details of an enum-type.

json_AtlasEnumElementDef.title: AtlasEnumElementDef
json_AtlasEnumElementDef.description: class that captures details of an enum-element.

json_AtlasStruct.title: AtlasStruct
json_AtlasStruct.description: Captures details of struct contents. Not instantiated directly, used only via AtlasEntity, AtlasClassification.

json_AtlasStructDef.title: AtlasStructDef
json_AtlasStructDef.description: class that captures details of a struct-type.

json_Operator.title: Operator
json_Operator.description:
Supported search operations
Logical comparision operators can only be used with numbers or dates
IN, LIKE, startsWith, endsWith, CONTAINS can only be used with strings or text

entityFilters.description: Entity attribute filters for the type (if type name is specified)

tagFilters.description: Tag attribute filters for the classification/tag (if tag name is specified)

attributes.description: Attribute values included in the results

json_SortType.title: SortType
json_SortType.description: to specify whether the result should be sorted? If yes, whether asc or desc.

json_Status.title: Status
json_Status.description: Status of the entity - can be active or deleted. Deleted entities are not removed from Atlas store.

xml_ns0_searchFilter.title: searchFilter
xml_ns0_searchFilter.description: Generic filter, to specify search criteria using name/value pairs.

xml_ns0_sortType.title: sortType
xml_ns0_sortType.description: to specify whether the result should be sorted? If yes, whether asc or desc.

xml_ns0_atlasClassification.title: atlasClassification
xml_ns0_atlasClassification.description: An instance of a classification; it doesn't have an identity, this object exists only when associated with an entity.

xml_ns0_atlasStruct.title: atlasStruct
xml_ns0_atlasStruct.description: Captures details of struct contents. Not instantiated directly, used only via AtlasEntity, AtlasClassification.

parameters.description: start offset of the result set (useful for pagination)

parameters.description: limit the result to only entities of specified type or its sub-types
